1
00:01:30,220 --> 00:01:32,980
Episode 30

2
00:01:34,150 --> 00:01:34,920
Wanzhi.

3
00:01:38,040 --> 00:01:38,790
I admit

4
00:01:39,840 --> 00:01:41,000
you're still

5
00:01:41,680 --> 00:01:42,950
a big shareholder.

6
00:01:43,640 --> 00:01:45,280
But the pledge ratio

7
00:01:46,200 --> 00:01:47,150
is pretty high.

8
00:01:48,640 --> 00:01:50,230
If the stock price suddenly crashes

9
00:01:51,430 --> 00:01:52,680
and your shares get liquidated,

10
00:01:54,400 --> 00:01:55,230
what will happen?

11
00:02:01,950 --> 00:02:03,480
Everyone at my company

12
00:02:03,510 --> 00:02:04,920
will stand with me

13
00:02:05,350 --> 00:02:06,840
and fight you.

14
00:02:07,510 --> 00:02:09,240
I know they're all loyal to you.

15
00:02:10,680 --> 00:02:12,080
But that's also your weak spot.

16
00:02:12,630 --> 00:02:14,400
If you hadn't

17
00:02:14,710 --> 00:02:15,750
handed out shares

18
00:02:15,870 --> 00:02:17,430
to all those workers,

19
00:02:18,310 --> 00:02:19,430
I'd never have a shot

20
00:02:19,470 --> 00:02:20,960
at taking you on.

21
00:02:21,520 --> 00:02:22,430
Now,

22
00:02:22,840 --> 00:02:23,750
you've lost

23
00:02:23,840 --> 00:02:25,080
complete control.

24
00:02:25,840 --> 00:02:27,150
It's only a matter of time

25
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:30,520
before someone else takes your spot.

26
00:02:36,310 --> 00:02:37,150
I promise

27
00:02:37,870 --> 00:02:39,430
I'll give you sufficient money.

28
00:02:40,190 --> 00:02:41,680
If you want to stay,

29
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:43,870
we can discuss

30
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:46,120
your title.

31
00:02:47,030 --> 00:02:47,910
Yan Ziwei,

32
00:02:48,630 --> 00:02:49,870
taking the company public

33
00:02:49,870 --> 00:02:51,310
was for its growth

34
00:02:51,630 --> 00:02:52,910
and for the future

35
00:02:53,030 --> 00:02:54,310
of nearly 2,000 employees.

36
00:02:55,470 --> 00:02:56,190
Right.

37
00:02:56,750 --> 00:02:58,000
They were

38
00:02:58,030 --> 00:02:58,870
factory workers.

39
00:02:59,400 --> 00:03:00,310
But they built

40
00:03:00,400 --> 00:03:01,240
this brand.

41
00:03:01,280 --> 00:03:02,680
They won't give it to you.

42
00:03:03,190 --> 00:03:04,470
And I will never

43
00:03:04,560 --> 00:03:05,800
make a compromise.

44
00:03:06,520 --> 00:03:08,080
If you want a fight,

45
00:03:09,520 --> 00:03:11,030
you've got one.

46
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:41,630
He's playing it smart.

47
00:03:42,030 --> 00:03:43,030
Even the authorities

48
00:03:43,080 --> 00:03:44,120
can't handle it.

49
00:03:44,750 --> 00:03:45,560
To put it bluntly,

50
00:03:45,910 --> 00:03:47,030
we're no match

51
00:03:47,030 --> 00:03:47,680
for them.

52
00:03:48,150 --> 00:03:49,120
If this goes on,

53
00:03:49,240 --> 00:03:50,960
the only loser will be Miao Toys

54
00:03:51,080 --> 00:03:51,960
and Fang Wanzhi.

55
00:03:53,910 --> 00:03:54,430
Juan,

56
00:03:54,750 --> 00:03:56,030
you're her best friend.

57
00:03:56,680 --> 00:03:57,470
Talk to her.

58
00:03:59,960 --> 00:04:01,280
A wise man knows when to yield.

59
00:04:01,360 --> 00:04:02,000
Sometimes

60
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:03,680
you just have to compromise

61
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:04,910
and even back down.

62
00:04:05,080 --> 00:04:06,240
To Wanzhi, the company

63
00:04:06,310 --> 00:04:07,240
is her kid.

64
00:04:07,280 --> 00:04:08,960
How could she possibly just give up?

65
00:04:09,310 --> 00:04:10,710
Throw yourself at a meat grinder,

66
00:04:10,710 --> 00:04:11,400
and your blood

67
00:04:11,520 --> 00:04:12,080
will only

68
00:04:12,080 --> 00:04:13,400
make it run smoother!

69
00:04:14,190 --> 00:04:15,560
If we want to turn this around,

70
00:04:16,190 --> 00:04:17,680
we can't rely on courage alone.

71
00:04:17,830 --> 00:04:18,870
We need chips.

72
00:04:19,310 --> 00:04:20,270
Our cash flow

73
00:04:20,310 --> 00:04:21,190
is insufficient.

74
00:04:21,310 --> 00:04:22,270
Keep holding on,

75
00:04:22,360 --> 00:04:23,830
and we'll go bankrupt!

76
00:04:24,310 --> 00:04:25,360
Overestimating ourselves

77
00:04:25,480 --> 00:04:27,000
means losing everything!

78
00:04:27,190 --> 00:04:29,040
We'll be walking away with nothing!

79
00:04:30,360 --> 00:04:32,270
Dignity matters more than money.

80
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:34,430
What do you want?

81
00:04:35,390 --> 00:04:37,070
You're on their side now?

82
00:04:37,480 --> 00:04:38,630
Becoming a traitor?

83
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:40,070
I didn't mean that.

84
00:04:40,950 --> 00:04:41,920
Wanzhi, calm down.

85
00:04:43,480 --> 00:04:44,630
Let me break down

86
00:04:45,160 --> 00:04:46,120
the situation.

87
00:04:46,190 --> 00:04:47,000
No need.

88
00:04:47,680 --> 00:04:48,600
You're just afraid of

89
00:04:48,630 --> 00:04:49,870
losing your stake,

90
00:04:49,870 --> 00:04:50,600
aren't you?

91
00:04:51,120 --> 00:04:52,040
When Yan Ziwei

92
00:04:52,190 --> 00:04:53,070
was pumping the stock,

93
00:04:53,160 --> 00:04:54,270
why didn't you sell?

94
00:04:54,510 --> 00:04:55,310
Serves you right!

95
00:04:57,240 --> 00:04:57,630
Gao Xiang,

96
00:04:58,190 --> 00:04:59,600
you've known me for years.

97
00:05:00,190 --> 00:05:01,950
Either you fight alongside me,

98
00:05:02,190 --> 00:05:03,830
or you leave now!

99
00:05:17,270 --> 00:05:19,920
(I feel like a stranger
in a strange land,)

100
00:05:20,720 --> 00:05:21,870
(just like years ago)

101
00:05:21,870 --> 00:05:23,680
(when I first came to Shenzhen.)

102
00:05:24,920 --> 00:05:25,630
(I feel)

103
00:05:25,630 --> 00:05:27,800
(the difference in this city.)

104
00:05:28,830 --> 00:05:30,360
(So familiar,)

105
00:05:31,160 --> 00:05:32,510
(yet so cold.)

106
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:35,750
(Gao Xiang says compromise is wisdom.)

107
00:05:36,560 --> 00:05:38,070
(But I've always believed)

108
00:05:38,600 --> 00:05:39,750
(a person's backbone)

109
00:05:40,120 --> 00:05:41,510
(can't go soft.)

110
00:05:56,270 --> 00:05:57,600
Why aren't you live-streaming?

111
00:05:57,870 --> 00:05:58,800
We don't have fans

112
00:05:59,120 --> 00:05:59,920
or a singer.

113
00:06:00,240 --> 00:06:01,190
Just playing for fun.

114
00:06:01,750 --> 00:06:03,630
Whoever wants to sing, we play.

115
00:06:04,120 --> 00:06:04,750
Lady,

116
00:06:04,950 --> 00:06:05,720
wanna sing a song?

117
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:18,720
♪Bitter sand♪

118
00:06:18,830 --> 00:06:21,240
♪Stings my face♪

119
00:06:21,750 --> 00:06:22,950
♪Like my father's words♪

120
00:06:23,070 --> 00:06:24,190
♪Like my mother's tears♪

121
00:06:24,360 --> 00:06:26,310
♪Forever etched in memory♪

122
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:28,630
♪As a boy♪

123
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:31,560
♪I'd wander alone by the sea♪

124
00:06:31,830 --> 00:06:34,160
♪Rolling up my pant legs♪

125
00:06:34,160 --> 00:06:36,160
♪Barefoot on the sand♪

126
00:06:36,870 --> 00:06:39,190
♪Always imagining another world♪

127
00:06:39,190 --> 00:06:41,390
♪At the ocean's end♪

128
00:06:41,830 --> 00:06:44,270
♪Always believing a brave sailor♪

129
00:06:44,270 --> 00:06:46,510
♪Is a true man♪

130
00:06:46,510 --> 00:06:50,920
♪Always looking weak and cowardly♪

131
00:06:51,510 --> 00:06:53,560
♪Yet whenever I was bullied♪

132
00:06:53,560 --> 00:06:56,160
♪I always heard a sailor say♪

133
00:06:56,160 --> 00:06:58,630
♪What's a little pain♪

134
00:06:58,630 --> 00:07:00,750
♪In the storm?♪

135
00:07:01,070 --> 00:07:03,630
♪Wipe your tears, don't be afraid♪

136
00:07:03,630 --> 00:07:05,830
♪At least we still have dreams♪

137
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:08,480
♪What's a little pain♪

138
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:10,680
♪In the storm?♪

139
00:07:11,040 --> 00:07:14,870
♪Wipe your tears, don't be afraid♪

140
00:07:16,120 --> 00:07:18,480
♪What's a little pain♪

141
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:20,680
♪In the storm?♪

142
00:07:20,870 --> 00:07:23,360
♪Wipe your tears, don't be afraid♪

143
00:07:23,510 --> 00:07:25,830
♪At least we still have dreams♪

144
00:07:26,040 --> 00:07:28,430
♪What's a little pain♪

145
00:07:28,510 --> 00:07:30,720
♪In the storm?♪

146
00:07:30,920 --> 00:07:33,390
♪Wipe your tears♪

147
00:07:33,430 --> 00:07:34,920
♪Don't be afraid♪

148
00:07:35,480 --> 00:07:36,000
Ms. Fang.

149
00:07:37,040 --> 00:07:38,040
Someone wants to see you.

150
00:07:38,360 --> 00:07:39,870
He's from Yu County.

151
00:07:45,750 --> 00:07:46,360
Wanzhi.

152
00:07:47,310 --> 00:07:48,240
Mr. Xiao!

153
00:07:49,720 --> 00:07:50,430
Please.

154
00:07:52,680 --> 00:07:53,480
Have some tea.

155
00:07:54,800 --> 00:07:55,680
What brings you here?

156
00:07:57,120 --> 00:07:58,160
My kid is in Shenzhen.

157
00:07:59,390 --> 00:08:00,600
So I figured I'd stop by.

158
00:08:03,270 --> 00:08:05,600
You've built such a big company.

159
00:08:06,870 --> 00:08:07,560
It's amazing.

160
00:08:09,750 --> 00:08:10,430
Busy?

161
00:08:12,160 --> 00:08:13,270
A bit.

162
00:08:18,390 --> 00:08:18,920
Wanzhi,

163
00:08:21,270 --> 00:08:22,920
can you come back to Yu County

164
00:08:25,430 --> 00:08:26,680
and see Mr. Meng off?

165
00:08:28,510 --> 00:08:29,360
My dad?

166
00:08:30,870 --> 00:08:31,830
What do you mean?

167
00:08:35,440 --> 00:08:36,550
I called him last weekend.

168
00:08:37,030 --> 00:08:38,150
He said he was writing.

169
00:08:38,910 --> 00:08:40,360
The Biography of Su Dongpo,

170
00:08:41,030 --> 00:08:41,790
right?

171
00:08:44,320 --> 00:08:44,960
Yes.

172
00:08:45,750 --> 00:08:46,870
What you saw before

173
00:08:49,080 --> 00:08:50,240
were his notes

174
00:08:50,240 --> 00:08:51,360
from his class.

175
00:08:53,030 --> 00:08:55,840
Mr. Meng is a cultured man.

176
00:08:56,240 --> 00:08:57,000
But he...

177
00:08:58,270 --> 00:09:00,030
never wanted to write a book.

178
00:09:01,440 --> 00:09:02,030
But...

179
00:09:02,840 --> 00:09:03,630
Three years ago,

180
00:09:04,440 --> 00:09:05,910
he was diagnosed with cancer

181
00:09:07,320 --> 00:09:08,200
in Shenzhen.

182
00:09:08,910 --> 00:09:11,030
You were busy with the IPO.

183
00:09:12,120 --> 00:09:13,910
He didn't want to distract you.

184
00:09:15,120 --> 00:09:15,870
So he took Miao

185
00:09:17,030 --> 00:09:18,200
back to Yu County.

186
00:09:19,360 --> 00:09:20,390
It was kept

187
00:09:21,390 --> 00:09:22,720
between just a few of us.

188
00:09:24,390 --> 00:09:25,440
He told us

189
00:09:26,030 --> 00:09:26,750
not to say a word.

190
00:09:27,630 --> 00:09:28,630
Especially to keep it

191
00:09:29,630 --> 00:09:30,600
from you.

192
00:09:31,320 --> 00:09:32,550
He didn't want you

193
00:09:32,550 --> 00:09:33,440
to see him in pain.

194
00:09:35,480 --> 00:09:36,440
And he didn't want you

195
00:09:36,440 --> 00:09:37,670
to suffer alongside him.

196
00:09:38,790 --> 00:09:40,630
But if you don't go back now,

197
00:09:42,670 --> 00:09:44,030
you might never see him again.

198
00:10:17,270 --> 00:10:18,000
Ms. Fang.

199
00:10:21,720 --> 00:10:22,480
Dad.

200
00:10:24,390 --> 00:10:25,200
A month ago,

201
00:10:26,150 --> 00:10:27,320
he asked to leave the hospital

202
00:10:27,550 --> 00:10:28,270
and go home.

203
00:10:32,200 --> 00:10:32,840
Wanzhi.

204
00:10:36,910 --> 00:10:38,030
This is Li,

205
00:10:38,910 --> 00:10:40,910
your mom's student.

206
00:10:42,360 --> 00:10:43,960
She comes every day to give him IVs.

207
00:10:46,480 --> 00:10:47,120
Liu

208
00:10:47,910 --> 00:10:49,750
works for the Bureau
of Retired Veteran Cadres.

209
00:10:50,790 --> 00:10:52,510
He visits Mr. Meng every few days.

210
00:11:26,870 --> 00:11:27,790
Dad.

211
00:13:21,150 --> 00:13:22,200
Mr. Meng!

212
00:13:26,390 --> 00:13:27,670
Mrs. Li, you're here.

213
00:13:28,960 --> 00:13:29,670
Wanzhi,

214
00:13:31,150 --> 00:13:32,200
Yudan said

215
00:13:32,390 --> 00:13:34,150
he's busy and can't make it back.

216
00:13:34,550 --> 00:13:35,790
That's infuriating.

217
00:13:58,080 --> 00:13:58,840
Wanzhi,

218
00:14:00,910 --> 00:14:01,630
don't worry.

219
00:14:02,960 --> 00:14:03,870
Even if

220
00:14:04,440 --> 00:14:05,120
you're busy,

221
00:14:06,030 --> 00:14:06,960
I'll come

222
00:14:07,960 --> 00:14:09,030
tend to

223
00:14:09,790 --> 00:14:11,320
their graves.

224
00:14:16,240 --> 00:14:17,200
Thank you.

225
00:14:24,750 --> 00:14:25,670
Thank you, everyone.

226
00:14:29,960 --> 00:14:30,630
Ms. Fang,

227
00:14:31,550 --> 00:14:33,320
Mr. Meng left a letter for you.

228
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:34,870
It's locked.

229
00:14:36,360 --> 00:14:37,720
He said you'd know

230
00:14:37,720 --> 00:14:38,840
which drawer it's in.

231
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:39,960
Here's the key.

232
00:15:09,840 --> 00:15:12,600
(Clouds meet rain, snow meets wind.)

233
00:15:13,030 --> 00:15:14,790
(Dusk meets the cloudless sky.)

234
00:15:15,390 --> 00:15:17,150
(Geese arrive as swallows leave.)

235
00:15:17,910 --> 00:15:19,750
(Birds rest while insects sing.)

236
00:15:20,600 --> 00:15:23,150
(A short sword, a mighty bow.)

237
00:15:23,510 --> 00:15:24,750
(Northern hills meet eastern shores.)

238
00:15:24,840 --> 00:15:25,480
(Good.)

239
00:15:25,870 --> 00:15:27,630
(Just write these,)

240
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:28,630
(okay?)

241
00:15:29,150 --> 00:15:30,030
(Com here.)

242
00:16:12,910 --> 00:16:13,910
(Wanzhi,)

243
00:16:15,240 --> 00:16:17,200
(when you read this,)

244
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:20,390
(my stubbornness)

245
00:16:21,600 --> 00:16:23,960
(has yielded to Death's final move.)

246
00:16:24,960 --> 00:16:26,120
(Don't be sad.)

247
00:16:27,910 --> 00:16:28,840
(In this life,)

248
00:16:28,960 --> 00:16:30,870
(I traded words with your mother)

249
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:34,200
(and battled the stigma
of a poor county.)

250
00:16:35,320 --> 00:16:37,320
(Against all odds,)

251
00:16:37,550 --> 00:16:40,030
(I completed the Jing River Bridge
on time.)

252
00:16:41,270 --> 00:16:43,750
(Under extreme difficulty, I exceeded)

253
00:16:43,910 --> 00:16:45,270
(my investment attraction targets.)

254
00:16:46,030 --> 00:16:48,750
(I found kinship with Su Dongpo)

255
00:16:49,750 --> 00:16:52,750
(and the joy of
teaching calligraphy to Miao.)

256
00:16:53,390 --> 00:16:54,670
(Abundant years)

257
00:16:55,440 --> 00:16:57,790
(and exultant spirit.)

258
00:16:58,510 --> 00:17:00,240
(I have no regrets.)

259
00:17:02,670 --> 00:17:03,670
(Do you remember)

260
00:17:04,480 --> 00:17:05,590
(when you were eight,)

261
00:17:06,270 --> 00:17:07,480
(the three of us)

262
00:17:08,270 --> 00:17:10,000
(planted an osmanthus tree)

263
00:17:10,240 --> 00:17:12,000
(in the government compound?)

264
00:17:12,830 --> 00:17:14,680
(I went to see it the other day.)

265
00:17:15,720 --> 00:17:19,400
(Last night, the wind
withered the leaves.)

266
00:17:20,310 --> 00:17:24,000
(yet the sweetness
was stronger than ever.)

267
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:28,830
(If Jingyu saw me writing like this,)

268
00:17:30,110 --> 00:17:32,200
(she'd laugh at me
and say I'm just posing.)

269
00:17:33,550 --> 00:17:34,750
(Here's a funny story.)

270
00:17:36,200 --> 00:17:36,920
(When I went to)

271
00:17:37,790 --> 00:17:39,440
(a poor village for work,)

272
00:17:40,640 --> 00:17:42,550
(she was also there to treat patients.)

273
00:17:43,270 --> 00:17:44,440
(A woman was in difficult labor.)

274
00:17:45,550 --> 00:17:47,000
(She was too busy)

275
00:17:47,030 --> 00:17:48,000
(to give me a glance.)

276
00:17:48,960 --> 00:17:50,830
(Her trousers were covered
in blood and dirt,)

277
00:17:51,400 --> 00:17:52,680
(yet she looked more beautiful)

278
00:17:52,790 --> 00:17:54,160
(than in her finest cheongsam)

279
00:17:54,510 --> 00:17:56,000
(at official events.)

280
00:17:57,480 --> 00:17:58,350
(I'll never forget)

281
00:17:59,200 --> 00:18:00,720
(that moment.)

282
00:18:02,110 --> 00:18:03,920
(One thing needs to be clear.)

283
00:18:04,880 --> 00:18:06,590
(I'm the one who named you.)

284
00:18:07,310 --> 00:18:09,000
(I insisted that you be a Fang.)

285
00:18:09,680 --> 00:18:10,790
(I wanted you to remember)

286
00:18:11,510 --> 00:18:13,000
(that the Fang family shed blood)

287
00:18:13,270 --> 00:18:15,160
(in the War of Resistance
against Japanese Aggression)

288
00:18:15,750 --> 00:18:17,590
(and gave everything to support)

289
00:18:17,880 --> 00:18:19,400
(the building of New China.)

290
00:18:20,400 --> 00:18:22,640
(When your grandpa
donated half his mountain)

291
00:18:22,720 --> 00:18:24,920
(to build a nursing home, he said)

292
00:18:25,920 --> 00:18:27,270
(good deeds)

293
00:18:28,070 --> 00:18:29,350
(leave a lasting fragrance.)

294
00:18:31,110 --> 00:18:32,480
(Now the fragrance)

295
00:18:33,510 --> 00:18:35,270
(is yours.)

296
00:18:37,110 --> 00:18:38,310
(The day)

297
00:18:38,750 --> 00:18:40,590
(Miao Toys rang that bell in Shenzhen,)

298
00:18:41,110 --> 00:18:42,110
(I spent the whole night)

299
00:18:43,070 --> 00:18:44,160
(bragging to)

300
00:18:44,310 --> 00:18:45,790
(my old buddies.)

301
00:18:47,550 --> 00:18:48,640
(But I also know)

302
00:18:49,590 --> 00:18:52,960
(business has its rises and falls.)

303
00:18:53,920 --> 00:18:55,350
(If you hit a wall,)

304
00:18:55,750 --> 00:18:57,400
(think of Su Dongpo.)

305
00:18:57,880 --> 00:19:01,200
(He didn't have that carefree spirit)

306
00:19:01,590 --> 00:19:04,590
(until after he was exiled.)

307
00:19:05,550 --> 00:19:07,160
(I have some good news for you.)

308
00:19:08,880 --> 00:19:09,640
(The co-op)

309
00:19:09,680 --> 00:19:11,310
(I've been helping since I retired)

310
00:19:12,440 --> 00:19:14,110
(won gold)

311
00:19:14,680 --> 00:19:15,830
(at Paris Design Week.)

312
00:19:17,310 --> 00:19:19,270
(Their inspiration)

313
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:21,440
(came from)

314
00:19:21,590 --> 00:19:23,160
(your toy robots.)

315
00:19:24,270 --> 00:19:25,270
(Are you happy?)

316
00:19:26,640 --> 00:19:28,200
(Please humor me.)

317
00:19:29,400 --> 00:19:30,240
(I have a request.)

318
00:19:31,550 --> 00:19:33,110
(I hope you soon find someone)

319
00:19:33,480 --> 00:19:35,270
(who you can talk business with)

320
00:19:35,960 --> 00:19:38,440
(and share a moonlit drink with.)

321
00:19:39,240 --> 00:19:40,270
(I think)

322
00:19:41,030 --> 00:19:42,200
(Gao Xiang is good.)

323
00:19:43,310 --> 00:19:44,160
(Also,)

324
00:19:45,110 --> 00:19:47,960
(Su Dongpo left behind
thousands of famous lines.)

325
00:19:49,270 --> 00:19:50,440
(My favorite line is)

326
00:19:51,110 --> 00:19:53,920
("Where the heart finds peace,
there is home.")

327
00:19:54,830 --> 00:19:56,350
(You left home young.)

328
00:19:57,270 --> 00:19:58,720
(Actually,)

329
00:19:59,680 --> 00:20:01,200
(this line suits you.)

330
00:20:02,110 --> 00:20:03,000
(And...)

331
00:20:04,110 --> 00:20:06,110
(So much to say.)

332
00:20:06,440 --> 00:20:08,750
(One letter doesn't seem enough.)

333
00:20:09,400 --> 00:20:12,030
(But I guess this is where it ends.)

334
00:20:12,790 --> 00:20:13,510
(I'm tired.)

335
00:20:14,550 --> 00:20:16,200
(One last thing.)

336
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:17,830
(Dongpo Pork)

337
00:20:18,400 --> 00:20:20,640
(gets its flavor from
the mix of fat and lean.)

338
00:20:21,350 --> 00:20:22,310
(Life is)

339
00:20:23,510 --> 00:20:25,070
(the same.)

340
00:20:26,680 --> 00:20:29,510
(Your loving father,)

341
00:20:30,550 --> 00:20:33,510
(Meng Siyuan.)

342
00:20:56,200 --> 00:20:56,750
Dad.

343
00:21:34,680 --> 00:21:36,110
You misunderstood Gao Xiang.

344
00:21:37,440 --> 00:21:40,240
He took all the money

345
00:21:40,640 --> 00:21:42,440
he cashed out from SkyMind

346
00:21:42,880 --> 00:21:43,480
and bought

347
00:21:43,480 --> 00:21:44,920
our shares.

348
00:21:45,790 --> 00:21:46,680
If not for

349
00:21:46,720 --> 00:21:47,640
his secret support,

350
00:21:48,310 --> 00:21:48,830
Yan Ziwei

351
00:21:48,830 --> 00:21:50,270
would have already won.

352
00:21:54,590 --> 00:21:55,480
Gao Xiang

353
00:21:55,550 --> 00:21:56,480
now holds

354
00:21:56,480 --> 00:21:58,200
3.7% of the shares.

355
00:22:08,030 --> 00:22:09,590
I was a mess that day,

356
00:22:11,440 --> 00:22:12,550
so I snapped.

357
00:22:16,110 --> 00:22:17,400
How's the stock doing lately?

358
00:22:18,270 --> 00:22:19,400
I haven't checked.

359
00:22:19,400 --> 00:22:20,350
And you never told me.

360
00:22:21,400 --> 00:22:22,030
Just say it.

361
00:22:23,000 --> 00:22:23,680
Tanked?

362
00:22:24,680 --> 00:22:25,790
I'm prepared.

363
00:22:27,200 --> 00:22:28,310
It's deadlocked.

364
00:22:31,680 --> 00:22:32,160
When I left,

365
00:22:32,270 --> 00:22:33,400
it was on the edge.

366
00:22:34,240 --> 00:22:35,510
Gao Xiang's shares

367
00:22:35,680 --> 00:22:37,270
couldn't have kept it going this long.

368
00:22:37,680 --> 00:22:39,200
A third party appeared

369
00:22:39,880 --> 00:22:41,440
and balanced out Hongwei Capital.

370
00:22:42,110 --> 00:22:43,640
Now it's a three-way stalemate.

371
00:22:44,030 --> 00:22:45,110
A third party?

372
00:22:48,880 --> 00:22:49,790
Who?

373
00:22:50,480 --> 00:22:51,240
No need to check.

374
00:22:51,790 --> 00:22:52,640
It's your brother.

375
00:22:54,790 --> 00:22:55,750
Xingke?

376
00:23:32,750 --> 00:23:33,350
Wanzhi,

377
00:23:33,880 --> 00:23:34,590
my condolences.

378
00:23:35,030 --> 00:23:35,720
I'm sorry

379
00:23:36,110 --> 00:23:37,750
I couldn't be there to see Mr. Meng off.

380
00:23:38,590 --> 00:23:40,270
He passed peacefully.

381
00:23:42,590 --> 00:23:43,550
Enough about that.

382
00:23:44,590 --> 00:23:45,790
I've only been gone a few days,

383
00:23:46,110 --> 00:23:47,160
and now you're

384
00:23:47,270 --> 00:23:47,960
Miao Toys's

385
00:23:48,000 --> 00:23:49,110
third largest shareholder.

386
00:23:50,070 --> 00:23:51,070
Remember the day

387
00:23:51,160 --> 00:23:52,640
the Shenxian Peak Supermarket opened?

388
00:23:53,000 --> 00:23:53,960
I wanted to invest,

389
00:23:54,960 --> 00:23:56,310
but you never let me.

390
00:23:57,350 --> 00:23:58,640
I thought about asking you

391
00:23:58,640 --> 00:23:59,880
a few times when I was strapped.

392
00:24:00,920 --> 00:24:01,880
But I sorted it out

393
00:24:01,920 --> 00:24:03,000
in the end.

394
00:24:03,510 --> 00:24:04,110
I didn't want

395
00:24:04,200 --> 00:24:05,310
to drag our relationship

396
00:24:05,400 --> 00:24:06,590
into your work.

397
00:24:07,310 --> 00:24:08,350
It would affect you.

398
00:24:10,480 --> 00:24:11,270
You've always

399
00:24:11,830 --> 00:24:13,070
looked out for me.

400
00:24:13,960 --> 00:24:15,030
You're no different.

401
00:24:15,680 --> 00:24:16,920
Your involvement

402
00:24:17,000 --> 00:24:18,160
eased the risk.

403
00:24:18,830 --> 00:24:20,480
But with that capital shark on our tail,

404
00:24:21,070 --> 00:24:21,920
we could still

405
00:24:21,920 --> 00:24:23,350
go under.

406
00:24:24,640 --> 00:24:25,960
How would you answer for that?

407
00:24:26,350 --> 00:24:27,070
This investment

408
00:24:27,110 --> 00:24:28,640
wasn't for short-term gains.

409
00:24:28,880 --> 00:24:30,030
We believe in

410
00:24:30,110 --> 00:24:31,240
the toy industry.

411
00:24:31,880 --> 00:24:32,510
My team and I

412
00:24:32,510 --> 00:24:33,510
did the research

413
00:24:33,640 --> 00:24:34,750
and convinced management.

414
00:24:35,310 --> 00:24:36,350
Or I couldn't have moved

415
00:24:36,400 --> 00:24:37,680
that much capital.

416
00:24:37,960 --> 00:24:39,070
How did you convince them?

417
00:24:43,030 --> 00:24:43,720
With this.

418
00:25:26,640 --> 00:25:27,310
Give it to me.

419
00:25:36,200 --> 00:25:37,590
How long did that report take?

420
00:25:38,160 --> 00:25:40,000
We spent two weeks on it.

421
00:25:40,550 --> 00:25:42,070
We'd been following it for a while,

422
00:25:42,400 --> 00:25:44,240
so we had a solid foundation.

423
00:25:45,480 --> 00:25:46,830
A capital firm is into

424
00:25:47,350 --> 00:25:48,310
the real economy now?

425
00:25:48,790 --> 00:25:49,830
The company's transforming.

426
00:25:50,240 --> 00:25:51,590
You're a public company

427
00:25:51,830 --> 00:25:53,000
with a solid position

428
00:25:53,070 --> 00:25:53,790
and potential.

429
00:25:53,790 --> 00:25:54,680
So we're interested.

430
00:25:55,830 --> 00:25:56,590
Don't get it wrong.

431
00:25:56,960 --> 00:25:58,440
We just want

432
00:25:58,640 --> 00:25:59,160
